Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization and analysis of user to access point association strategies in heterogeneous cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and modeling of the association cells, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the impact of association strategies on network performance, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
